  "prompt": "How much time does Wipro takes to send a DOJ after the background verification is done?",
  "response": "The time Wipro takes to send a **Date of Joining (DOJ)** after background verification is completed can vary depending on several factors, such as the role, location, and internal processes. Generally, it may take **1 to 3 weeks** after the background verification is successfully completed for Wipro to finalize your DOJ and communicate it to you.\n\nHowever, this timeline is not fixed and could be longer in some cases, especially if there are additional checks or delays in the documentation process. If you have not received your DOJ within this timeframe, it\u2019s advisable to follow up with the HR or recruitment team at Wipro for updates.\n\nTo ensure a smooth process, make sure to respond promptly to any requests for additional information or documents during the background verification process.",
